# The client pulls the three.js stack (@react-three/fiber/drei/postprocessing +
# postprocessing/n8ao) whose `three` peer ranges conflict, so a strict `npm ci`
# fails with ERESOLVE. Resolve peers leniently everywhere (CI and local installs)
# instead of having to remember `--legacy-peer-deps` on every install.
legacy-peer-deps=true
